1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,540
 Well, during my senior year of university,

2
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:05,980
 I had this incredible experience.

3
00:00:05,980 --> 00:00:10,980
 I went to chapel, and the Holy Spirit convicted me

4
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:14,180
 that I was missing the opportunities

5
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:16,020
 in which God wanted to use me.

6
00:00:16,020 --> 00:00:20,980
 And I actually could see them flashing by in front of me.

7
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:24,480
 And so I prayed a simple prayer.

8
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:29,860
 I said, "Lord, I don't wanna miss the opportunities

9
00:00:29,860 --> 00:00:32,720
 "anymore in which you wanna use me."

10
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:36,520
 And I genuinely meant it.

11
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:42,900
 Now, a few days later, a friend of mine calls me

12
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:46,740
 and says, "Tim, I wanna talk about Jesus."

13
00:00:46,740 --> 00:00:49,780
 Who says that on the phone?

14
00:00:49,780 --> 00:00:50,980
 You know, but my friend did.

15
00:00:50,980 --> 00:00:55,180
 And so I was like, "Oh, this is the opportunity.

16
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,900
 "I'm not gonna miss it."

17
00:00:56,900 --> 00:01:00,540
 And so I started sharing my faith with my friend,

18
00:01:00,540 --> 00:01:05,340
 which was something that I hadn't done really before.

19
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:08,180
 And then over a period of time,

20
00:01:08,180 --> 00:01:10,500
 I think it was like eight, nine months,

21
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:15,500
 he ended up becoming a Christian, a father of Jesus.

22
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:19,400
 And I was so encouraged to experience God use me.

23
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:21,320
 I was so encouraged.

24
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:25,940
 Now, all this happened my senior year.

25
00:01:25,940 --> 00:01:29,820
 I graduated from university and I started my first job

26
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:31,540
 working for a paint company.

27
00:01:31,540 --> 00:01:33,460
 And I was still on fire.

28
00:01:33,460 --> 00:01:37,420
 I had this spiritual mountaintop experience,

29
00:01:37,420 --> 00:01:40,680
 but that only lasted for a while.

30
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:44,420
 So the company that I was working for,

31
00:01:44,420 --> 00:01:48,740
 they moved me to a location where I didn't know anyone.

32
00:01:48,740 --> 00:01:50,820
 I didn't have a church.

33
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:53,060
 And I found myself going through actually

34
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:55,540
 one of the darkest times of my Christian journey

35
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:58,020
 that I've experienced even up to this date,

36
00:01:58,020 --> 00:02:01,900
 where I wasn't attending church or community.

37
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:04,220
 So I didn't really have people to fellowship with.

38
00:02:04,220 --> 00:02:06,140
 You know, we even talked about that.

39
00:02:06,140 --> 00:02:08,460
 Natasha shared about fellowshipping with others in prayer.

40
00:02:08,460 --> 00:02:09,940
 I didn't have that.

41
00:02:09,940 --> 00:02:14,140
 I was just isolated.

42
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:17,420
 I didn't have any friends around me to speak into my life,

43
00:02:17,420 --> 00:02:18,260
 to encourage me.

44
00:02:18,260 --> 00:02:21,660
 I was hanging around with people that were encouraging me

45
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:24,340
 to do things that were not great, which I then did.

46
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:27,140
 So I also made some bad choices.

47
00:02:27,140 --> 00:02:31,260
 And I really got to the point where I was not the person,

48
00:02:31,260 --> 00:02:33,820
 I knew I was not the person I wanted to be.

49
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:36,300
 And I definitely was not the person

50
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:39,000
 that God called me to be.

51
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,100
 But I felt stuck.

52
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,020
 I felt stuck.

53
00:02:42,020 --> 00:02:47,180
 Now, following Jesus, it's not always easy.

54
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:50,860
 That there are pressures and challenges

55
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:54,620
 that we all experience, where we have to figure out

56
00:02:54,620 --> 00:02:56,260
 how to navigate them and what to do.

57
00:02:56,260 --> 00:02:58,620
 For me, the pressure and the challenge

58
00:02:58,620 --> 00:03:01,180
 was not having Christian community,

59
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:04,780
 hanging around with a crowd that was not encouraging me

60
00:03:04,780 --> 00:03:06,140
 in the right direction.

61
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:08,980
 That was my pressure and my challenge.

62
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:11,100
 And I caved.

63
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:14,400
 I wasn't who I wanted to be.

64
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:18,380
 But for others, maybe it's pressure from your job.

65
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:20,020
 Maybe there's something about your job

66
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:22,660
 that's asking you to do something you do not want to do.

67
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:23,680
 You knew it was not right.

68
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,740
 You know it does not honor Jesus.

69
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:29,440
 But you're experiencing this pressure to give in to that.

70
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:32,920
 Maybe it has something to do with pressure from family.

71
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,700
 Sometimes our families, they might love us,

72
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:37,900
 but they might still ask us to do things that are not good.

73
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:40,140
 And it creates pressure on us.

74
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:43,540
 Maybe it's a pressure in relationship,

75
00:03:43,540 --> 00:03:46,540
 or we're sick.

76
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:48,300
 And that creates pressure for us also

77
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:51,900
 to out of desperation to maybe make some choices

78
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,420
 that are not good.

79
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:57,180
 But what do we do?

80
00:03:57,180 --> 00:04:02,180
 How can we stand firm in our faith in those moments?

81
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:04,800
 So what I wanna do with you,

82
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,880
 I wanna explore this with you today.

83
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:10,380
 How can I cultivate a resilient faith

84
00:04:10,380 --> 00:04:15,180
 that will help me stand firm in my commitment to Jesus,

85
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:17,460
 regardless of what pressure comes?

86
00:04:18,380 --> 00:04:19,780
 You know, how do you do that?

87
00:04:19,780 --> 00:04:21,220
 And can we even do that?

88
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:24,220
 Can we even do that?

89
00:04:24,220 --> 00:04:25,420
 So that's what we're gonna explore

90
00:04:25,420 --> 00:04:27,760
 through our Bible passage today.

91
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:30,660
 We're in the book of Daniel.

92
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:35,660
 We're in the final sermon of the sermon series, Unshaken.

93
00:04:35,660 --> 00:04:37,700
 So basically we're talking about unshaken faith,

94
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,780
 and how do you actually get that?

95
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:42,520
 It's nice to hear about that Daniel had it, right?

96
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,940
 But how do we have that?

97
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:48,380
 And so we're gonna look at the final vision

98
00:04:48,380 --> 00:04:51,620
 that God gives Daniel.

99
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:55,180
 And this vision runs from chapter 10

100
00:04:55,180 --> 00:04:57,780
 all the way through chapter 12,

101
00:04:57,780 --> 00:05:00,460
 which is a lot of biblical texts.

102
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:02,280
 We're not gonna cover all of it,

103
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:04,360
 but I just wanna walk you through some parts

104
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:08,980
 before we pick up the passage

105
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:10,420
 that we're gonna look at today.

106
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:15,420
 So basically it is the third year of King Cyrus.

107
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:17,620
 So there's been a shift.

108
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:20,060
 Babylon, the empire has fallen.

109
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:22,380
 The Persian empire has been established.

110
00:05:22,380 --> 00:05:26,140
 Israel, the seven years of exile are over.

111
00:05:26,140 --> 00:05:27,200
 They've returned home.

112
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,160
 They're three years about home.

113
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:33,580
 But things didn't turn out the way they hoped for

114
00:05:33,580 --> 00:05:35,260
 when they got home.

115
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:36,460
 And for them, they thought,

116
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:39,100
 "We go back, it's gonna be great.

117
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:41,780
 "We're gonna rebuild the temple.

118
00:05:41,780 --> 00:05:44,580
 "The kingdom of Israel is gonna flourish.

119
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:45,460
 "It's gonna be amazing."

120
00:05:45,460 --> 00:05:47,380
 But that's not what happened.

121
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:49,700
 Actually, they struggled to rebuild the temple.

122
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,580
 They stopped.

123
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:55,540
 There was ongoing ransacking of the people that moved back.

124
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:57,940
 And so they're going through an extreme period

125
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:01,800
 of difficulty and persecution and struggle.

126
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:07,660
 And so Daniel, he seeks God in prayer and fasting 21 days.

127
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:12,660
 And the vision that God gives Daniel is a response

128
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:16,680
 to this prayer and the seeking out of this desperate place.

129
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:21,420
 And the vision that he gets is,

130
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:25,340
 first of all, it's about empires that come and that fall.

131
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:28,540
 And they basically, the vision start right

132
00:06:28,540 --> 00:06:29,660
 where Daniel's life is,

133
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:31,860
 and they move several hundred years forward.

134
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:33,820
 And it's actually quite incredible.

135
00:06:33,820 --> 00:06:38,820
 The last king sort of that Daniel's vision is about

136
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:41,800
 is Antiochus IV Epiphanes.

137
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:45,060
 It's a hard name to say.

138
00:06:45,060 --> 00:06:46,100
 Epiphanes, there we go.

139
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:48,440
 Antiochus IV Epiphanes, there we go.

140
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:55,380
 And this king was a horrendous ruler.

141
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:59,580
 He really hated God's people.

142
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:01,740
 And he sacrificed, so this is like history.

143
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:03,420
 You can read about it in history.

144
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:08,420
 He sacrificed a pig in the Jerusalem temple.

145
00:07:08,420 --> 00:07:10,340
 He oppressed the people,

146
00:07:10,340 --> 00:07:14,160
 tried to get them to commit idolatry by worshiping Zeus,

147
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,580
 so one of the Greek gods.

148
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:18,380
 And so this was a horrible period of persecution.

149
00:07:18,380 --> 00:07:20,860
 So Daniel, the vision that God gives Daniel

150
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:23,780
 is of the rise and fall of all these empires,

151
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:26,300
 including Antiochus.

152
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:28,380
 And so this is amazing.

153
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:32,060
 God actually has foretold what was gonna happen.

154
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:36,500
 But then the vision jumps to even a further future.

155
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:39,420
 And what is described there has not yet happened.

156
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:43,320
 And it's also a period,

157
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,220
 it talks about it's at the time of the end,

158
00:07:45,220 --> 00:07:48,160
 so what we would call tribulation or end times.

159
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:50,460
 And so he describes that.

160
00:07:50,460 --> 00:07:53,060
 And we're picking up in chapter 12

161
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:57,840
 about this period of difficulty and persecution

162
00:07:57,840 --> 00:08:00,940
 and see what vision God shared with Daniel.

163
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:02,500
 That was a very long intro,

164
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,780
 but that's the context, all right?

165
00:08:04,780 --> 00:08:06,740
 So let's go to Daniel 12,

166
00:08:06,740 --> 00:08:09,820
 we're starting in verse one, it says this.

167
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:11,780
 At that time,

168
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:14,060
 so again, talking about this time of distress,

169
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,620
 Michael, the great prince

170
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:18,220
 who protects your people will arise.

171
00:08:18,220 --> 00:08:19,820
 There will be a time of distress

172
00:08:19,820 --> 00:08:21,300
 such as has not happened

173
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:24,480
 from the beginning of nations until then.

174
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,540
 But at that time, your people,

175
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:29,500
 everyone whose name is found written in the book

176
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:31,020
 will be delivered.

177
00:08:31,020 --> 00:08:33,460
 Multitudes who sleep in the dust of the earth

178
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:36,980
 will awake, some to everlasting life,

179
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:40,300
 others to shame and everlasting contempt.

180
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:43,500
 Those who are wise will shine like brightness

181
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:44,420
 of the heavens,

182
00:08:44,420 --> 00:08:46,820
 and those will lead many to righteousness

183
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:49,240
 like the stars forever and ever.

184
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:54,700
 But you, Daniel, roll up and seal the words of the scroll

185
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,420
 until the time of the end.

186
00:08:56,420 --> 00:09:00,200
 Many will go here and there to increase knowledge.

187
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:06,600
 Now this passage, it gives us a powerful vision

188
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,360
 of two things, two contrasts.

189
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:11,940
 One is distress on the one hand,

190
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:15,140
 and then on the other hand, it's a vision of hope.

191
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:16,060
 It's both.

192
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:19,100
 So let's look at the distress,

193
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,320
 'cause it talks about that there will be a time

194
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:23,620
 of distress such as has not happened

195
00:09:23,620 --> 00:09:26,300
 from the beginning of the nations until then.

196
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:30,100
 Now, you and I, we've been around here for a while,

197
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:33,280
 and we know of things, horrible things that have happened.

198
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:36,340
 Well, that time's gonna be worse

199
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:38,800
 than the horrible things that we know have happened.

200
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:42,180
 Now let that sink in, right?

201
00:09:42,180 --> 00:09:43,880
 That's actually quite scary,

202
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:48,100
 quite hard to fathom even, how can it even be worse?

203
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:58,700
 But the Bible is honest about sin, about suffering.

204
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:02,020
 You know, it doesn't hide that.

205
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:05,660
 So this is something that will happen,

206
00:10:05,660 --> 00:10:07,480
 and God's people will be persecuted.

207
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:10,640
 But even in the midst of that,

208
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:12,460
 there's already here a glimmer of hope,

209
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:14,540
 and then hope is further described.

210
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:17,220
 It says that Michael, the great prince

211
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:18,620
 who protects your people, will arise.

212
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:23,620
 Now, Michael is an angel, and he will fight on our behalf

213
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,260
 he will fight on behalf of God's people

214
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:28,020
 in the spiritual realm.

215
00:10:28,020 --> 00:10:33,060
 So we might feel like we're alone,

216
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:35,140
 but God is battling on our behalf.

217
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:36,940
 You know, he is fighting for us.

218
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:41,360
 So it's like the first word of hope, but then it continues.

219
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:44,900
 Because the deliverance is further described,

220
00:10:44,900 --> 00:10:47,180
 it talks about this continuing in verse one,

221
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:49,160
 but at that time, your people,

222
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:51,940
 everyone whose name is found written in the book,

223
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:53,420
 will be delivered.

224
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:57,620
 So everyone who belongs to God will be delivered.

225
00:10:57,620 --> 00:11:00,380
 Everyone who has faith in Jesus,

226
00:11:00,380 --> 00:11:04,340
 who has fellowship with Jesus, will be delivered.

227
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:08,860
 Now that is amazing,

228
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:13,260
 especially as you're facing, you know, such horrible,

229
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:16,820
 unimaginable persecution and hardship.

230
00:11:16,820 --> 00:11:18,700
 You know, God will deliver us.

231
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:22,160
 And then that deliverance is explained in verse two.

232
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:25,340
 What that deliverance looks like even further.

233
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:28,260
 It says this multitude to sleep in the dust of the earth

234
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:31,060
 will awake some to everlasting life,

235
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:33,680
 others to shame and everlasting contempt.

236
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:40,020
 Now, sleeping in the dust is a metaphor for being dead.

237
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:44,980
 And arising is that God will raise every person.

238
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:48,100
 And we will stand before God,

239
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:50,940
 and some will receive everlasting life,

240
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:53,640
 and some there will be shame and everlasting contempt.

241
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:59,180
 And for those of us who are raised to everlasting life,

242
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:01,740
 you know, that is amazing.

243
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:04,140
 This is the, actually, this is the clearest passage

244
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:07,360
 in the Old Testament where it talks about resurrection.

245
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:11,980
 In the New Testament, of course, we receive more about that.

246
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:15,920
 But this is amazing hope that even death,

247
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:18,860
 that even in the face of death,

248
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:20,540
 or even if we have experienced death,

249
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:25,540
 God can bring everything to a great resolution.

250
00:12:25,540 --> 00:12:31,060
 You know, he can bring justice to us.

251
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:34,500
 He can raise us to a life

252
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,860
 where we are in his everlasting kingdom,

253
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:40,620
 where all tears will be wiped away,

254
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:41,960
 now where there will be no more shame,

255
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,180
 there will be no more suffering.

256
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:45,140
 And that is incredible news.

257
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:48,940
 That is incredible good news.

258
00:12:48,940 --> 00:12:53,940
 But it does also talk about shame and everlasting contempt.

259
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:59,580
 Now, usually, you know, we don't talk about that that much,

260
00:12:59,580 --> 00:13:01,140
 or if you create a sermon series

261
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:02,580
 and you're not preaching straight through a book,

262
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:05,940
 a lot of times you, you know, for whatever reason,

263
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:09,400
 you don't come choose those passages to talk about.

264
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,940
 But I felt like today I actually should say

265
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:13,380
 a little bit more, maybe how we can think about this

266
00:13:13,380 --> 00:13:15,620
 as everlasting contempt and as shame,

267
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:17,220
 which is basically hell, right?

268
00:13:18,140 --> 00:13:20,660
 And so what I'm sharing comes from a book

269
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:22,740
 from C.S. Lewis, "The Great Divorce,"

270
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:25,180
 so that's where these ideas are from.

271
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,900
 But basically, a lot of us, we wonder,

272
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,460
 how can a loving God, you know,

273
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:33,100
 send people to everlasting contempt and shame?

274
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:35,220
 You know, how does that fit together?

275
00:13:35,220 --> 00:13:39,780
 And one way, or which I find the most helpful way

276
00:13:39,780 --> 00:13:43,500
 to think about is God honors our choices.

277
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:46,220
 You know, he honors our choices.

278
00:13:46,420 --> 00:13:51,060
 If we choose to live in rebellion and apart from God,

279
00:13:51,060 --> 00:13:53,740
 at this final judgment, God affirms that

280
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:56,580
 and just allows us to continue in the choice

281
00:13:56,580 --> 00:13:59,540
 that we have been consistently making throughout our lives.

282
00:13:59,540 --> 00:14:04,460
 And so it shows that there's a real weightiness,

283
00:14:04,460 --> 00:14:08,320
 there's a real seriousness to the choices that we make.

284
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:13,540
 If we choose to be in a relationship with God,

285
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:15,700
 if we surrender to Jesus, you know,

286
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:18,740
 we get to experience this everlasting life.

287
00:14:18,740 --> 00:14:21,700
 But if we choose to live lives apart from God,

288
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:23,780
 well, God honors that.

289
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:28,020
 He proclaims our judgment and we live in that separation

290
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:31,980
 and sin continues to unravel in all its fullness.

291
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:37,340
 Now, I hope this is helpful.

292
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:40,100
 I usually, it's not what we focus on

293
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:41,580
 or spend a lot of time on talking about,

294
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:42,740
 but I think it's important,

295
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:44,580
 and as a pastor, it's my responsibility

296
00:14:44,580 --> 00:14:46,220
 to talk to you about these things.

297
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:49,940
 And so there it is, and I hope it's helpful.

298
00:14:49,940 --> 00:14:53,900
 Now, I do wanna say that for us, of course,

299
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,980
 and also from, I think, consistent with the New Testament,

300
00:14:55,980 --> 00:14:57,940
 we don't try to scare people

301
00:14:57,940 --> 00:15:00,780
 with everlasting contempt and shame.

302
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:02,620
 And I don't think it's fear

303
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:04,900
 that really drives people to God.

304
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:08,700
 It's God's love, it's his mercy, you know, it's his grace.

305
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:13,420
 And that's what we seek to share and emphasize.

306
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:16,980
 And in Romans 2, 4, it says that it's God's kindness

307
00:15:16,980 --> 00:15:18,980
 that leads us to repentance.

308
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:21,100
 It's when we get a glimpse, you know,

309
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:24,660
 of just God's incredible mercy and love for us,

310
00:15:24,660 --> 00:15:28,060
 that that is what turns our hearts towards him.

311
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:31,180
 And so that's our approach as a mind church,

312
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:34,100
 and I think it's biblically, you know, what we see.

313
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:40,300
 But going back, so we have this incredible hope

314
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:43,220
 that Daniel's given, and people who are suffering,

315
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:44,700
 people who are dying,

316
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:48,780
 and there's this promise, you know,

317
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:52,700
 that they will be raised

318
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:55,100
 for those who are faithful to him, to everlasting life.

319
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:58,260
 So this is an incredible word for a suffering,

320
00:15:58,260 --> 00:15:59,820
 a struggling community,

321
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:03,300
 and it's an incredible word for anyone who's facing death,

322
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,980
 which at one point in time, we all will.

323
00:16:05,980 --> 00:16:07,340
 And from the New Testament, of course,

324
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:12,340
 we know that Jesus, that he died and rose.

325
00:16:12,660 --> 00:16:15,460
 And because he died and rose, we too,

326
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:18,700
 all those who belong to him will also die and rise.

327
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:23,020
 1 Corinthians 15 talks about the harvest,

328
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:24,540
 that it's the first fruit,

329
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:27,300
 that Jesus' resurrection is the first fruit.

330
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:28,940
 That means when the first fruit appears,

331
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:30,840
 that means there's more fruit to come.

332
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:34,420
 And so we can be confident because Jesus rose

333
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:38,540
 that we too will rise, you know, at this time.

334
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:39,700
 And so as Christians,

335
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:43,340
 we even have a stronger confidence and clarity

336
00:16:43,340 --> 00:16:47,260
 than Daniel and God's people at that time had.

337
00:16:47,260 --> 00:16:50,260
 But let's continue with the vision.

338
00:16:50,260 --> 00:16:54,100
 So then there's a third part where, in this vision,

339
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:58,260
 Daniel, he's, and that speaks of glorification.

340
00:16:58,260 --> 00:16:59,600
 Let me explain that.

341
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:04,140
 Verse three says that those who are wise

342
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:06,940
 will shine like the brightness of the heavens,

343
00:17:06,940 --> 00:17:08,720
 and those who lead many to righteousness

344
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:10,520
 like the stars forever and ever.

345
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:17,140
 And there is, when God's saving work is completed in us,

346
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:22,100
 you know, when we're completely made whole,

347
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:25,700
 we not only get to enjoy God's glory,

348
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:29,180
 but in some ways we get to also share in it.

349
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:33,020
 And biblically, when it talks about salvation,

350
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:34,100
 there's different parts.

351
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:37,620
 It talks about as past, as present, and as future.

352
00:17:37,620 --> 00:17:39,400
 Past is you were justified.

353
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,520
 There's a legal declaration that was made.

354
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:42,820
 You are righteous.

355
00:17:42,820 --> 00:17:44,160
 You are God's child.

356
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,800
 You are forgiven.

357
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:48,440
 That's past, justification.

358
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:52,320
 Then there is ongoing, that is sanctification.

359
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:54,200
 You are being made holy.

360
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:57,560
 You are being conformed to the image of Christ.

361
00:17:57,560 --> 00:18:01,320
 And then finally, there is glorification

362
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:04,920
 when God's work in us is completed.

363
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:08,000
 You know, we are fully who he created us to be.

364
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:13,980
 And so this is what this is picturing in a beautiful way.

365
00:18:13,980 --> 00:18:16,820
 But I also want you to notice one thing there.

366
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:19,740
 It describes what a faithful life looks like.

367
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:23,660
 'Cause it says that it's those

368
00:18:23,660 --> 00:18:26,540
 who lead many to righteousness.

369
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:29,860
 So part of living a faithful life and standing firm,

370
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:31,260
 you know, in relation with Jesus,

371
00:18:31,260 --> 00:18:34,780
 also involves leading many to righteousness.

372
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:36,160
 So that means, what does that mean?

373
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:38,460
 Well, it means we connect people with God

374
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:41,740
 through how we live ourselves, through what we say to them.

375
00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:46,560
 And so we get to be part of this redeeming,

376
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:48,260
 redemptive work of God

377
00:18:48,260 --> 00:18:51,680
 that we can lead many to righteousness.

378
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:53,280
 And as we connect them with Jesus,

379
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:55,700
 as we model what it means to love our neighbors,

380
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,720
 to serve the marginalized,

381
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:00,460
 and to share the love of God with others,

382
00:19:00,460 --> 00:19:02,740
 and as we share it with them as well.

383
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,660
 And that is part of this faithfulness

384
00:19:04,660 --> 00:19:06,080
 that God invites us into.

385
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:08,980
 A life that is not just centered around

386
00:19:08,980 --> 00:19:11,740
 fulfilling only our dreams

387
00:19:11,740 --> 00:19:13,500
 and not caring about anyone else.

388
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:15,740
 You know, it's a life that is able

389
00:19:15,740 --> 00:19:17,860
 to also care and invest in others.

390
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:23,100
 Well, let's continue and go to the final part of the vision.

391
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,920
 And I'm just gonna, after we read it,

392
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,880
 it's a little bit of a longer section,

393
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,940
 I'm just gonna really briefly talk about it

394
00:19:28,940 --> 00:19:30,020
 because there's a lot in it

395
00:19:30,020 --> 00:19:32,900
 and there's no way to unpack all of that, okay?

396
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:33,860
 But let's read it.

397
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:36,560
 So continuing in verse five, it says this.

398
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:39,020
 Then I, Daniel, looked,

399
00:19:39,020 --> 00:19:41,940
 and there before me stood two others,

400
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:43,760
 one on this bank of the river

401
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:45,820
 and one on the opposite bank.

402
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:48,660
 One of them said to the man clothed in linen,

403
00:19:48,660 --> 00:19:50,540
 "Who was above the waters of the river?

404
00:19:50,540 --> 00:19:51,860
 How long will it be

405
00:19:51,860 --> 00:19:56,300
 before these astonishing things are fulfilled?"

406
00:19:56,300 --> 00:19:57,420
 The man clothed in linen,

407
00:19:57,420 --> 00:19:59,140
 who was above the waters of the river,

408
00:19:59,140 --> 00:20:02,780
 had lifted his right hand and his left hand towards heaven.

409
00:20:02,780 --> 00:20:06,300
 And I heard him swear by him who lives forever,

410
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:10,900
 saying, "It will be for a time, times and a half a time,

411
00:20:10,900 --> 00:20:15,240
 when the power of the holy people has been finally broken,

412
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:17,100
 all these things will be completed."

413
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:21,180
 I heard, but I did not understand.

414
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:24,820
 So I asked, "My Lord, what will the outcome of all this be?"

415
00:20:24,820 --> 00:20:26,780
 He replied, "Go your way."

416
00:20:26,780 --> 00:20:28,740
 Daniel, because the words are rolled up

417
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:31,980
 and sealed until the time of the end.

418
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:36,020
 "Many will be purified, made spotless and refined,

419
00:20:36,020 --> 00:20:38,740
 but the wicked will continue to be wicked.

420
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:41,160
 None of the wicked will understand,

421
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:44,160
 but those who are wise will understand.

422
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:48,380
 From the time that the daily sacrifice is abolished

423
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:53,220
 and the abomination that causes desolation is set up,

424
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:56,460
 there will be 1,290 days.

425
00:20:56,460 --> 00:20:58,060
 Blessed is the one who waits for

426
00:20:58,060 --> 00:21:01,020
 and reaches the end of 1,335 days.

427
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:06,540
 As for you, go your way till the end.

428
00:21:06,540 --> 00:21:08,540
 You will rest.

429
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:10,140
 And then at the end of this,

430
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:15,140
 you will rise to receive your allotted inheritance."

431
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:20,700
 Now, this vision of Daniel,

432
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:24,140
 I think it ends in a very helpful,

433
00:21:24,140 --> 00:21:26,220
 but also maybe puzzling way.

434
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:31,420
 So it's helpful because we hear,

435
00:21:31,420 --> 00:21:34,080
 let me rephrase that.

436
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:37,840
 So it's helpful and puzzling.

437
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:42,420
 Daniel says, "I don't understand all of this."

438
00:21:42,420 --> 00:21:43,660
 Right?

439
00:21:43,660 --> 00:21:45,940
 He says, "I heard, but I did not understand."

440
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:48,700
 And I think there is some comfort in that

441
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:51,180
 because there is a lot in there,

442
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:55,300
 a lot of the details especially that is hard to understand.

443
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:59,920
 And I, of course, this also has to do with,

444
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:03,360
 as I shared two weeks ago, it's apocalyptic literature.

445
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:05,660
 There's a lot of symbolism and things.

446
00:22:05,660 --> 00:22:08,080
 We can understand the main idea,

447
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:10,520
 but in some of the details, it gets tricky

448
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:11,940
 and it's not always easy to understand.

449
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:13,520
 But God, by his Holy Spirit,

450
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:15,960
 helps us to understand what the main purpose is

451
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:17,440
 of what he's saying.

452
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,960
 And so I think there's some comfort in that

453
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,640
 that we don't always understand everything perfectly

454
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:22,900
 or every detail, right?

455
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:26,560
 The two questions about visions,

456
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:28,200
 there's two questions about the vision that I asked.

457
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,240
 One is how long?

458
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,800
 And what will the outcomes of all this be?

459
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:37,760
 And there's very cryptic answers to those questions, right?

460
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:40,440
 It's like times and times and half time.

461
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:41,400
 And then there's numbers.

462
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:43,240
 I felt like a little bit, it's like Cantonese lesson

463
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,520
 when I tried to read the numbers,

464
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:48,860
 you know, 1,290 days and 1,335 days.

465
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:53,800
 So what's the point of that?

466
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:54,640
 Now,

467
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:58,600
 the point of it

468
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:04,160
 is that God understands what these numbers mean,

469
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:07,760
 that he has numbered these days.

470
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:11,120
 He is in charge, sovereignly in charge of these events.

471
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:13,180
 He knows when they will unfold.

472
00:23:13,180 --> 00:23:18,360
 And because, you know, he knows because he is in charge,

473
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:20,920
 because he is Lord over all history,

474
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:24,520
 you know, we can rest assured.

475
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:26,000
 So that's the meaning of this,

476
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:28,480
 even if you don't understand the details of it.

477
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,880
 But that's the big picture,

478
00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:35,880
 you know, that because God is sovereign and in charge,

479
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:38,960
 because he numbers all days, you know,

480
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:43,840
 his purposes in our lives, his purposes for God's people,

481
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:47,640
 he will accomplish them and no one can stop that.

482
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:49,480
 Yes.

483
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:55,200
 So then Daniel, he's twice instructed, go your way.

484
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,160
 And first when I read this,

485
00:23:56,160 --> 00:24:00,120
 I felt like it was like, shut up, Daniel, stop asking.

486
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:02,200
 But that's not what this means.

487
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:04,680
 Actually, it's really reassuring Daniel.

488
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:11,280
 And God is reassuring him, hey, you've prayed,

489
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:12,920
 I've given you a solution for God's people

490
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,520
 who are struggling, who are suffering,

491
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,280
 who are going through difficulty.

492
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:21,280
 And you're wondering, you know, how to think of this

493
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:22,360
 and how to handle all this.

494
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,400
 Well, I've spoken to you,

495
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:26,240
 I've given you a vision of my sovereignty,

496
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:29,680
 I've given you a vision of the hope that you have,

497
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:31,960
 that your people have.

498
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:36,480
 And now, instead of being caught up in maybe how,

499
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:38,560
 in exactly when all this will fall down,

500
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:41,880
 you now live faithfully, you now follow me,

501
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:44,600
 you now do the things that I asked you to do

502
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,760
 in your day to day life.

503
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:48,400
 Now go your way.

504
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:52,120
 And there's also an incredible promise there in verse 13.

505
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:54,680
 And it says, "As for you, go your way till the end,

506
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:56,680
 "you will rest and then at the end of the days,

507
00:24:56,680 --> 00:25:00,440
 "you will rise to receive your allotted inheritance."

508
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:04,120
 The promise is you will rest, he will die,

509
00:25:04,120 --> 00:25:06,960
 you will rise, you will be raised to new life,

510
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:10,320
 and then you will receive your allotted inheritance.

511
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:15,320
 God will bless you as you are part of this new world.

512
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:20,280
 And part of his everlasting kingdom.

513
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,320
 So that's incredible, and that's a true promise

514
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:26,600
 for all of us who follow Jesus.

515
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:31,600
 You know, we will rest, we will rise, and we will receive.

516
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:38,320
 Now, earlier I asked a question,

517
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:40,360
 and you might be wondering, like, what in the world,

518
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:42,200
 how does all of this connect with this question

519
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:44,120
 that Tim asked earlier?

520
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:47,080
 How can I cultivate a resilient faith

521
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:50,280
 that will help me stand firm in my commitment to Jesus,

522
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:52,880
 regardless of what pressure comes?

523
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:55,560
 And how does this vision that Daniel receives

524
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:57,620
 speak into this question?

525
00:25:57,620 --> 00:26:03,680
 Well, Daniel had hope in God.

526
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:08,320
 He had hope that God was sovereignly in charge

527
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:10,200
 over all of history.

528
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:13,120
 And this hope was greater than any difficulty,

529
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:17,320
 any persecution, any struggle, any challenge,

530
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:22,080
 any pain, even greater than death.

531
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:27,200
 So this is incredible hope.

532
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:30,640
 And this is hope that we can only find in God.

533
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:35,160
 And you see, when we receive that kind of hope,

534
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:40,480
 it really frees us, 'cause we no longer need

535
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:43,640
 to be overwhelmed by our circumstances.

536
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:46,240
 They might still weigh on us, and we shouldn't pretend

537
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:48,720
 like we're not struggling with things,

538
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:53,720
 but we can be confident in that God is at work,

539
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:57,640
 that he will bring about his purposes in our lives,

540
00:26:57,640 --> 00:27:01,400
 that they will unfold, he will make them happen.

541
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:06,400
 And that really frees us to not so much be focused

542
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:08,480
 on these things, but to focus on the things

543
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:13,000
 that God asks us to do, to be about the things of God.

544
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:16,640
 Jesus would call it seeking first the kingdom of God.

545
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:19,780
 Having this hope frees us to seek first the kingdom of God,

546
00:27:19,780 --> 00:27:22,760
 and for God to add all these other things unto us.

547
00:27:22,760 --> 00:27:26,040
 So that's incredible.

548
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,040
 And the same is true for us.

549
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:30,960
 God wants to give us this hope, this incredible hope

550
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:32,520
 that he is sovereign, that he rules,

551
00:27:32,520 --> 00:27:33,800
 that he's in charge of our lives

552
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:35,520
 as you are going through difficulties,

553
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:38,420
 as you are experiencing pressures on your faith,

554
00:27:38,420 --> 00:27:41,360
 that might be crushing you, that are overwhelming you.

555
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:45,400
 He wants you to see that he is sovereignly at work

556
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,640
 in your life, that you are not alone,

557
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:50,680
 that he is with you, and that his purposes,

558
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:53,280
 for those who are faithful, he will unfold them

559
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:56,760
 in your life, because he is faithful.

560
00:27:56,760 --> 00:28:01,220
 Now, when we talk about hope, our understanding of hope,

561
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:03,800
 and the biblical understanding of hope is quite different.

562
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:05,440
 Our understanding of hope is,

563
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:10,180
 I hope tomorrow will be sunny so I can go hiking.

564
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:12,980
 So that's a wish, right?

565
00:28:12,980 --> 00:28:14,460
 I wish that tomorrow the weather's gonna be good

566
00:28:14,460 --> 00:28:15,700
 so I can go hiking.

567
00:28:15,700 --> 00:28:18,500
 I like hiking, I haven't hiked in a long time.

568
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:19,460
 But I hope.

569
00:28:19,460 --> 00:28:25,180
 But biblical hope is not wishful thinking.

570
00:28:25,180 --> 00:28:28,540
 It's a deep confidence in God's character,

571
00:28:28,540 --> 00:28:30,880
 his promises, and his sovereignty.

572
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:36,920
 And so when we hope in this way,

573
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,440
 we're not just wishfully thinking,

574
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:41,360
 it is rooted and based in who God is,

575
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:43,400
 and in our experience of God.

576
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:47,880
 And so you might wonder, how do I get this kind of hope?

577
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:49,840
 Like, what do you do?

578
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:53,820
 Well, first of all, you have to know Jesus,

579
00:28:53,820 --> 00:28:57,020
 'cause this hope is only found in a relationship with God.

580
00:28:57,020 --> 00:28:59,920
 So that's the beginning.

581
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:01,360
 But then what about beyond that?

582
00:29:01,360 --> 00:29:04,780
 Well, now, let's think about that.

583
00:29:04,780 --> 00:29:06,420
 If you think about Daniel's life,

584
00:29:06,420 --> 00:29:10,300
 was he always, did he always have this resilient faith

585
00:29:10,300 --> 00:29:11,780
 and this firm commitment?

586
00:29:11,780 --> 00:29:14,100
 You know, right when he was born,

587
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:20,020
 or early in life, did he have this resilience faith

588
00:29:20,020 --> 00:29:22,060
 you know, that we read about,

589
00:29:22,060 --> 00:29:23,700
 and that is so inspiring to us

590
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:25,260
 when we read the book of Daniel.

591
00:29:25,260 --> 00:29:26,320
 I don't think he did.

592
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:31,780
 I think it's a process that this faith is built.

593
00:29:31,780 --> 00:29:38,760
 And so how do we, how do we engage this process?

594
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:41,480
 Well, we also see that in Daniel's life.

595
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:47,400
 He chose, so he was deported from Israel to Babylon.

596
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:52,480
 Then he had to be part of the king's court

597
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:55,760
 where he was, you know, supposed to learn for three years

598
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:59,560
 and receive all his wisdom, Babylonian wisdom and everything.

599
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:01,560
 He was supposed to eat the choice food,

600
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:05,160
 and he chose not to defile himself, you know,

601
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:07,360
 by eating the foods that were offered to idols

602
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:09,080
 and that were not kosher.

603
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:11,980
 And he chose to obey the Mosaic law.

604
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:15,640
 And so through his choice, he's stepping out in faith.

605
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:18,040
 Earlier, think about "Spirit Lead Me."

606
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:19,480
 I don't remember the rest of the lyrics.

607
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,760
 I'm sure you know.

608
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:21,960
 The ocean song, right?

609
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:23,520
 Remember, "Trust us without borders."

610
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:25,700
 So he was stepping out in faith,

611
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:28,920
 but he didn't know what was gonna happen.

612
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:31,320
 I mean, the eunuch gave him 10 days,

613
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:33,120
 I think that's what it was, 10 days,

614
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:39,320
 of eating vegetables, and then God showed up.

615
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:40,800
 They were healthy, they were better,

616
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:42,600
 and the eunuch allowed him to just continue

617
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:43,800
 eating vegetables.

618
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:46,360
 And that's what happens when we step out in faith,

619
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:49,680
 when we're obedient to what God asks us to do

620
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:50,840
 with the little things that we know

621
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:52,680
 he's asking us to be obedient in.

622
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,280
 God shows up.

623
00:30:55,280 --> 00:31:01,480
 So growing in hope and faith,

624
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:05,480
 it's a process that you can engage in every day

625
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:09,860
 through obeying, doing what you know God asks you to do.

626
00:31:09,860 --> 00:31:13,360
 That's how we build hope.

627
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:16,640
 It's like through daily obedience to God

628
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:18,560
 and the things that he shows us to be obedient in.

629
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,520
 I don't know what he's showing you to be obedient in,

630
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:21,360
 but you know.

631
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:24,560
 So just be obedient in that,

632
00:31:24,560 --> 00:31:26,480
 and then as you're obedient in that,

633
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:27,720
 God will show up.

634
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:30,640
 He will let you know that he's there with you.

635
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:33,680
 Sometimes he provides and removes whatever is going on.

636
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:36,080
 Sometimes he just helps us to walk through it.

637
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,360
 You know, it can be different,

638
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:41,560
 but he will show up, and he does it time and time again.

639
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:43,960
 So as we continue to place our faith in him,

640
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:45,840
 as we continue to walk with him,

641
00:31:45,840 --> 00:31:50,840
 God will continue to show himself to you.

642
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:53,680
 You know, that he is faithful,

643
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:58,000
 that when we trust him, you know, that he shows up,

644
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,600
 'cause he cannot do it, it says in scripture,

645
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:02,680
 he cannot do anything else but be faithful.

646
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:04,480
 And so because God is faithful,

647
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:08,040
 we can be faithful, and we can grow in faithfulness.

648
00:32:08,040 --> 00:32:12,120
 You know, and it's something that's always by his grace.

649
00:32:12,120 --> 00:32:14,360
 It's always because the Holy Spirit is working on us

650
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:16,200
 as we take these, our feeble steps,

651
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:18,440
 and a lot of times we fumble around,

652
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:22,160
 but he can build this strong, resilient faith

653
00:32:22,160 --> 00:32:26,280
 that can stand firm in their commitment to Jesus,

654
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:28,840
 and he wants to build this faith in us.

655
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:31,280
 So I don't know earlier when I shared, like,

656
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:33,360
 you know, where you are in this journey,

657
00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:35,080
 if you're right now feeling a lot of pressure,

658
00:32:35,080 --> 00:32:37,640
 if there's a lot of struggles and difficulties,

659
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:42,120
 and you just really need to, like, grab hold of this hope.

660
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:46,880
 Well, the way that you do it is by just surrendering

661
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,560
 to Jesus, by doing what he asks you to do,

662
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:52,080
 and by seeing how he continues and continues

663
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:54,720
 and continues and continues to show up for you.

664
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:55,960
 Now, I was thinking about my own life.

665
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:57,600
 How have I experienced that?

666
00:32:57,600 --> 00:33:02,420
 Earlier, I started off with a story of,

667
00:33:02,420 --> 00:33:08,840
 in chapel, like, when I, you know, God convicted me

668
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:10,000
 that I was missing the opportunities

669
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:10,840
 which God wanted to use me,

670
00:33:10,840 --> 00:33:13,440
 so I started sharing my faith with a friend.

671
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:15,380
 I didn't know the Bible very well.

672
00:33:15,380 --> 00:33:18,120
 I was scared of having that conversation,

673
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:19,640
 'cause I didn't, what if my friend asked me

674
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:22,320
 difficult questions, guess what he did?

675
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:25,080
 And I had to then figure out what to say,

676
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:26,980
 or to say I don't know.

677
00:33:26,980 --> 00:33:28,960
 But it was amazing in that process,

678
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,520
 this was like, you know, seven, eight, nine months,

679
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:34,520
 there was times when I was reading something,

680
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:37,120
 maybe a day or two before, and then suddenly it was

681
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:39,560
 what came up in the conversation, you know,

682
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:42,080
 and then I could use it in this conversation.

683
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:44,680
 So I experienced God provide all along the way

684
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:47,040
 in that conversation, even.

685
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:50,280
 So when we step out in faith, God shows up.

686
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:55,000
 Another way of experiences is when I,

687
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:57,120
 so I was working for, at that time,

688
00:33:57,120 --> 00:34:01,800
 Morgan Stanley felt called to serve God,

689
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:03,360
 but it was a little bit ambiguous,

690
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:04,500
 I didn't know exactly what that meant,

691
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:07,120
 I just knew God wanted me to shift and do something else.

692
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:11,400
 And it was such a strong experience that I quit my job.

693
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:15,080
 And I was like, okay, actually that Sunday night

694
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:17,240
 I went into my office, I cleared out my office,

695
00:34:17,240 --> 00:34:18,960
 and then next day in jeans I went to my boss

696
00:34:18,960 --> 00:34:22,160
 and told him, "Sorry, I need to leave, God has called me."

697
00:34:22,160 --> 00:34:25,000
 Then he told me, "Okay, I wish you all the best,

698
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:28,000
 "don't shop at another investment firm in the next few months."

699
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:28,840
 (laughs)

700
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:33,840
 So, but, and then I didn't have anything,

701
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:35,600
 I didn't know what I was doing,

702
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:37,600
 it was like, I told my parents,

703
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:40,540
 and they were like, "You made the biggest mistake

704
00:34:40,540 --> 00:34:41,840
 "of your life." (laughs)

705
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:43,080
 That's what they told me.

706
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:47,880
 And, you know, but God showed up,

707
00:34:47,880 --> 00:34:50,360
 like he brought, my parents came around,

708
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:52,720
 they saw that God had worked in my life,

709
00:34:52,720 --> 00:34:56,540
 he led me on what to do next, and he provided.

710
00:34:56,540 --> 00:35:01,680
 And then, one thing that I do refer to here quite frequently

711
00:35:01,680 --> 00:35:04,280
 in a difficult and a painful time,

712
00:35:04,280 --> 00:35:09,280
 I was lost, most difficult time of my life.

713
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:10,580
 I didn't know what to do.

714
00:35:10,580 --> 00:35:15,820
 And I, a friend of mine, a pastor, he's like,

715
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:19,060
 "Tim, just focus on following Jesus.

716
00:35:19,060 --> 00:35:21,060
 "Like you can't control everything that happens,

717
00:35:21,060 --> 00:35:24,720
 "but you just focus on following Jesus."

718
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:28,680
 And that's what I try to do, you know, day in and day out,

719
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:33,240
 and then God met me along the way and he provided.

720
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:34,800
 'Cause when we step out in faith,

721
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:38,760
 when we do the things that God asks us to, he shows up.

722
00:35:39,440 --> 00:35:41,400
 And so he has done it in my life,

723
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,880
 and as I've gotten older, I'm more convinced of that,

724
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:47,080
 I have a greater hope, 'cause I have experienced

725
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:49,360
 God's faithfulness in a greater way,

726
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:51,280
 and I know he can do it in your life

727
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:53,560
 and has done it in many of your lives.

728
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:56,780
 But so if you wanna grow a resilient faith

729
00:35:56,780 --> 00:36:00,680
 that allows you to stand up, it starts with

730
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:04,280
 just ongoing surrendering and obedience

731
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:06,040
 to Jesus in your day to day.

732
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,800
 That's where you build it, not in the big moments

733
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:09,760
 when suddenly you need this massive faith,

734
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:12,380
 but in the little things in the day to day.

735
00:36:12,380 --> 00:36:15,000
 And Daniel's faith is not just for superheroes,

736
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:18,180
 it's for every single person who knows Jesus.

737
00:36:18,180 --> 00:36:19,880
 Now God can give you that faith

738
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:26,260
 to live lives of radically serving him and for his purposes.

739
00:36:26,260 --> 00:36:29,820
 And he shows up when we do that.

740
00:36:29,820 --> 00:36:33,420
 So I wanna invite the worship team to come.

741
00:36:33,420 --> 00:36:36,340
 (breathing deeply)

742
00:36:36,340 --> 00:36:44,540
 And I had this statement, it's because God is loving,

743
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:48,660
 faithful, sovereign, and in charge.

744
00:36:48,660 --> 00:36:52,500
 You know, we can go our way to the end unshaken,

745
00:36:52,500 --> 00:36:54,100
 faithfully following him.

746
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:57,660
 Now it's because of who God is,

747
00:36:57,660 --> 00:37:00,400
 not out of our own strength, not because of who we are,

748
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,980
 but it's because who God is that we even

749
00:37:01,980 --> 00:37:03,020
 can live in this way.

750
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:05,820
 It's by his grace, it's by his mercy.

751
00:37:05,820 --> 00:37:07,860
 And he wants us to see that.

752
00:37:07,860 --> 00:37:09,980
 He wants us to know that.

753
00:37:09,980 --> 00:37:12,940
 And he's inviting us even today here

754
00:37:12,940 --> 00:37:16,740
 to take steps of faith in the things

755
00:37:16,740 --> 00:37:18,780
 that he's asking us to do.

756
00:37:18,780 --> 00:37:21,520
 And so many times we're not available or we're scared,

757
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:26,660
 but he wants to lift our eyes to him and say, trust me.

758
00:37:26,660 --> 00:37:29,060
 Just like any, it's like a relationship too.

759
00:37:29,060 --> 00:37:32,180
 You get to, with a friend you say we're gonna meet

760
00:37:32,180 --> 00:37:33,300
 at this time, this point in time,

761
00:37:33,300 --> 00:37:35,540
 you go there and your friend's there.

762
00:37:35,540 --> 00:37:38,620
 Okay, you learn, oh, I can trust this person.

763
00:37:38,620 --> 00:37:40,700
 You know, and then as they do that 10 times, 20 times,

764
00:37:40,700 --> 00:37:42,860
 and you know, yeah, this is a person that shows up.

765
00:37:42,860 --> 00:37:45,300
 Well, it's that in a similar way it's with God.

766
00:37:45,300 --> 00:37:48,600
 You know, he is faithful, he shows up, he will provide.

767
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:54,980
 And as I was, I guess, preparing for today,

768
00:37:54,980 --> 00:37:56,540
 I felt like there's two things

769
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:58,160
 that God is inviting us into.

770
00:37:59,140 --> 00:38:03,100
 The first thing is, you know, where today

771
00:38:03,100 --> 00:38:05,200
 is actually God asking you to be faithful?

772
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:09,540
 What's that little thing that God is asking you

773
00:38:09,540 --> 00:38:11,540
 to faithfully follow Jesus?

774
00:38:11,540 --> 00:38:13,640
 Now, how can you be obedient to him today?

775
00:38:13,640 --> 00:38:18,260
 'Cause it's the little things that then later on

776
00:38:18,260 --> 00:38:20,620
 allows us to do it also in the big moments.

777
00:38:20,620 --> 00:38:21,940
 We don't know when they come,

778
00:38:21,940 --> 00:38:23,980
 but it's the little things that prepare that faith,

779
00:38:23,980 --> 00:38:26,780
 that build that resilient faith in our hearts.

780
00:38:27,700 --> 00:38:31,220
